Generation after generation kept this fire fountain going, day after day, year after year.
When people needed embers for their homes they'd take some and in return they'd throw some firewood in.
Eventually, everone forgot how to start a fire
and then, a fateful day, the fire was gone
and nobody could start it again.
Deep below the ground fire still burns
But nobody dares to venture there
